            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " API is a programming interface to the Security Server and its policy database. This API facilitates access control to restricted areas of the operating system and allows you to restrict a user’s access to particular features in your macOS app. Use authorization services in:"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "unorderedList",
          "items": [
            {
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": "Software that restricts access to its own tools"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": "Applications that call system tools"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": "Software installers that install privileged tools or require access to restricted areas of the operating system"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "As shown in Figure 1, the Security Server is a daemon running in the operating system that provides a trusted implementation of various security protocols, including authorization computation. In turn, the Security Server relies on the Security Agent to interface with users when authentication is needed. Thus an app can verify credentials (usernames and passwords) without ever accessing them directly. This authorization process also allows the means of authentication to change in the future (such as adding Touch ID) without your having to modify your app."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "image",
              "identifier": "media-2891901",
              "metadata": {
                "anchor": "2891901",
                "title": "Figure 1",
                "abstract": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Authorization services provide an interface to the Security Server"
                  }
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": []
        },
        {
          "type": "aside",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "For a simplified, class-based version of this API, consider using the "
                },
                {
                  "type": "reference",
                  "isActive": true,
                  "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/securityfoundation/sfauthorization"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " class instead. When you need a user interface that enables display and control of the current authorization state for a particular set of rights, use the "
                },
                {
                  "type": "reference",
                  "isActive": true,
                  "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/securityinterface/sfauthorizationview"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " class."
                }
              ]
            }
          ],
          "style": "note",
          "name": "Note"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": []
        },
        {
          "type": "aside",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "The Authorization Services API is not supported within an App Sandbox because the API allows privilege escalation."
                }
              ]
            }
          ],
          "style": "important"
        }
      ]
    }
